{"word":"H5645 - עָב - ʻâb - awb - Clay","slug":"H5645","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עָב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻâb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>awb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Clay"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05D1; - &#x201B;a&#x0302;b</b> - <i>awb</i><p/>Masculine and feminine; from <a href=\"#/H5743\">H5743</a>; properly an <i>envelope</i>, that is, <i>darkness</i> (or <i>density</i>, <a href='B:140 4:17'>2Ch 4:17</a>); specifically a (scud) <i>cloud</i>; also a <i>copse</i>: - clay, (thick) cloud, X thick, thicket. Compare <a href=\"#/H5672\">H5672</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5743\">H5743</a>"}]}